{
  "stem": "17526.3",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 106.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "There were specific orders by Himmler to ship us to Tyrol Mountains and to shoot us all because they were afraid that we would be escaping, surviving the war, and we will tell the atrocities.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And I remember the life, the nights on those trains.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Every morning, people were-- were-- were-- were just dropping dead.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "They put us 120 to 150 in this wagon, no food.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And there was a lot of noise.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And one time, one night the guy came in, one of the guard men, and he just hit people on the head with a rifle.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And he hit me.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "He-- he hit my head-- my shoulder and I couldn't move my arms for a couple of days.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "He broke something or whatever, just to quiet the sound because the noise was unbearable and the stench.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "The hunger pangs, the-- the-- absolutely-- there-- there's no words to describe it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "I-- I can only say one thing, people there were in it are impossible to-- to tell it, and the people who were not in it cannot possibly believe it, that those situations could have existed.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Anyway, on the eighth day, we-- all of a sudden, we felt the air, we sensed it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "There were rumors.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Where the rumors came from, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "But this was one long train with a lot of wagons.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And there were several trains on these rails from all the camps to be shipped away.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And we realized that we're going back and forth the same because we looked out and we saw the same landmarks.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "And we realized that we are not getting anyplace, we are-- and from this, people assumed that we may be trapped, we may be encircled, which was the truth.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "But it was hard to believe.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
